            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1692024534394-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the skin off your <strong>smoked mackerel fillet[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and discard the skin</p><p>Tear the <strong>smoked mackerel </strong>into rough pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1692024540761-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1692024540761-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1692024540761-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1692024540761-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1692024540761-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fresh tagliatelle </strong>to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the tagliatelle for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tagliatelle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1692024546015-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1692024546015-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1692024546015-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1692024546015-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1692024546015-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> dill & chives</strong> finely</p><p>Combine the juice of your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>zingy</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Toss the <strong>shredded lettuce </strong>in the <strong>zingy dressing</strong>, then set this aside until serving – this is your<strong> zingy salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1692024551315-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1692024551315-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1692024551315-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1692024551315-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1692024551315-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>tagliatelle is cooked, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until it starts to sizzle slightly</p><p>Add the <strong>torn smoked mackerel</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1692024562010-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1692024562010-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1692024562010-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1692024562010-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1692024562010-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> drained tagliatelle </strong>and<strong> </strong>a few splashes of the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> then increase the heat to high</p><p>Add the <strong>soft cheese </strong>and cook for 1-2 min, stirring until everything is combined and the sauce begins to stick to the pasta</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if the sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1692024616568-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1692024616568-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1692024616568-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1692024616568-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1692024616568-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Squeeze in the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> and add <strong>half </strong>your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later) with<strong> half</strong> the<strong> chopped dill & chives</strong> (save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>smoked mackerel tagliatelle</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1692024625908-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1692024625908-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1692024625908-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1692024625908-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1692024625908-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoked mackerel tagliatelle</strong> with the<strong> zingy salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>reserved chopped dill & chives </strong>all over and then season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
